title: May 26, 1951
cardSubtitle: President John F. Kennedy says he will send astronauts to the moon by 1970.

title: Jan. 26, 1962
cardSubtitle: Unmanned Ranger sent to crash into moon but misses target.

title: Nov. 6, 1966
cardSubtitle: Second of five U.S. satellites sent to orbit, map moon.

title: Jan. 27, 1967
cardSubtitle: Moon probe makes soft landing near crater Tycho. Photos, soil samples taken.

title: Oct. 11, 1968
cardSubtitle: First manned flight of Apollo 7 spacecraft

title: Feb. 19, 1970
cardSubtitle: U.S.S.R. fails fourth attempt to launch a moon rocket

title: April 11, 1970
cardSubtitle: Apollo 13 moon mission aborted when oxygen tank explodes

title: May 18, 1969
cardSubtitle: Apollo 15 makes fourth landing. First use of the lunar rover vehicle
